@startuml git-refs
title Git refs — named pointers under `.git/refs/`

skinparam monochrome false
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam rectangle {
    BackgroundColor #FAFAFA
    BorderColor #666
    RoundCorner 6
}

rectangle ".git/refs/" as ROOT #F4F4F4

rectangle "refs/heads/*\n\nLocal branches.\nmain, feature-X, ...\n\n**Used by:** git log, git checkout,\nGitHub file browser, `git clone`." as HEADS #D9EDFF

rectangle "refs/remotes/<remote>/*\n\nRemote-tracking branches.\norigin/main, upstream/main, ...\n\n**Used by:** git fetch, git pull,\nshown as 'origin/main' in git log." as REMOTES #D9EDFF

rectangle "refs/tags/*\n\nImmutable named commits.\nv1.0, release-2026-04, ...\n\n**Used by:** git tag, git checkout v1.0,\nGitHub Releases page." as TAGS #D9EDFF

rectangle "refs/pull/<n>/head\n\nGitHub-managed PR refs.\nCreated automatically when a PR opens.\n\n**Used by:** `gh pr checkout`,\nhidden from the normal branch list." as PULL #FFF8D6

rectangle "refs/dolt/data\n\n**Dolt's custom namespace.**\nHolds the chunk store of a SQL DB.\n\n**Used by:** dolt push / dolt clone.\nInvisible to GitHub UI and `git clone`." as DOLT #C4E2AC

ROOT -down-> HEADS
ROOT -down-> REMOTES
ROOT -down-> TAGS
ROOT -down-> PULL
ROOT -down-> DOLT

note bottom
  Any tool can create refs under a custom prefix.
  The refs namespace is extensible — that's the whole trick.
end note

@enduml
